{
  "stem": "13483.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I think, mostly, young Jewish boys, maybe even girls, at that time, they were, I think, quite idealistic about what was happening.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think we only saw some sort of-- we championed, I think, the Communist party, maybe, because it seemed to be the only party in England at the time that was prepared to fight fascism at the time.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We never knew about Israel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Palestine was just a distant land, as far as I was concerned.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't think it was a case of being Jewish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was mainly we were socialists.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And what was happening again, in Spain, and what was happening in England as well, I think we found the only salvation we really had was to belong to a party that was prepared to fight the fascists at the time.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I think most parents at the time, especially they came from the [INAUDIBLE], from Poland and Russia, did attach really any importance to it, mainly because, I suppose, they were glad to have come to England, you know?",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were allowed to come in in England as immigrants.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Both my mother and father did.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Till-- till-- right to their dying day, I don't think they ever spoke perfect English.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't really know what I wanted to be at that time when jobs were a little scarce, I think.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If they weren't scarce, I couldn't really make up my mind.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Although, I was always interested in radio and, you know, mechanical things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Dreams?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I dreamed of getting married, being-- becoming a rich man, but [LAUGHS] it didn't always turn out like that.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I left school at 14.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
